column1: From My Family to Yours  Happy Thanksgiving. https://t.co/qnVwHBhXTX
Happy Birthday to President-elect @JoeBiden and to my big sister Hazel. Birthdays are Blessings!
https://t.co/FdQkv4yrhJ
Congratulations to President-Elect @JoeBiden and Vice President-Elect @KamalaHarris. We shattered so many glass ceilings. We have a lot of work to do and looking forward to #buildbackbetter.

As we continue to watch the results come in I promise that we will fight to count EVERY vote. America is great because the voice of the people is our ultimate foundation. That voice will be heard—and I pray that @JoeBiden and @KamalaHarris will be the PEOPLE'S choice. https://t.co/OUbDLRxrqs

Serving as your Congresswoman has been an incredible privilege. I am deeply honored to have earned your trust for a third term. In the months and years ahead I will keep fighting so that every one of us can live in safety freedom and prosperity. With all my heart thank you.

When I joined the Orlando Police Department I did it because I wanted to help people. I never knew that over three decades of public service I would meet my husband raise a family here in Central Florida and be elected your Congresswoman.

After being sworn into Congress in 2017 thousands of women gathered in DC to ensure that women's issues continue to be heard. Thank you to all the women who have paved the path for equal rights and ensure we have the right to vote. Now more than ever your voice is needed. https://t.co/SBqF90VD5D https://t.co/sTyijijlKJ

In 1968 Shirley Chisholm became the first African American woman elected to Congress. She also ran for president in 1972. Her election inspires so many African American women that they can one day follow in her footsteps. https://t.co/SBqF91ddXb https://t.co/HBzwjJXDo1

Alice Paul along with Lucy Burns formed the National Women's Party (NWP). Paul Burns and the NWP were determined to put pressure on the government to ensure women had the right to vote and proposed an Equal Rights Amendment to be added in the U.S. Constitution. https://t.co/SBqF90VD5D

In July 1848 the women's rights movement was officially formed at the Seneca Falls Convention. Thanks to Elizabeth Cady Stanton and so many others involved in planning this convention that led to a movement that lives on. https://t.co/SBqF90VD5D

100 years ago the 19th amendment granting women the right to vote was adopted into the U.S. Constitution. Today we celebrate Women's Equality Day honoring all those who fought for the right to vote. Throughout the day I will honor the legacy of those before us.

I will continue to work to make the American Dream an attainable reality for every person in our country and continue the struggle for a more perfect union.

The #BidenHarris2020 ticket promises to restore America's faith that we can defeat covid-19 save our crippled economy restore honor and integrity to the WH protect the rights liberty and safety of the American people and expand access to health care and opportunity for all.
In this time of crises we deserve leadership that will not only put America back on track but #BuildBackBetter.

For a little girl who grew up poor Black and female in the South to be considered during this process has been an incredible honor. I feel so blessed.
